oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">in the=
 business of</a> selling =E2=80=9CFrederick=E2=80=99s of Hollywood intimate=
s products, sleepwear and loungewear products, swimwear and swimwear access=
ories products, and costume products=E2=80=9D over the internet. It had an =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25638771.285655/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzAwMDE3MDc5MTkvMDAwMTQ5M=
zE1MjIxMDEyMTMzL2Zvcm0yMC1mLmh0bSNvXzAwMg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1e629ba7=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D=
"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;">annual loss</a> of 73 million New Zealand dollars on revenue of 8=
0 million NZD. (Naked is listed in the U.S., is incorporated in Australia, =
sells mostly online, and keeps its books in New Zealand dollars. I wouldn=
=E2=80=99t worry about it!)</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At the end of J=
anuary 2021, all of that was also true except that Naked=E2=80=99s stock pr=
ice was up 759% for the month. Why? I guess the short answer is =E2=80=9Cme=
me stock.=E2=80=9D People on Reddit decided it would be fun to buy shares o=
f an online lingerie retailer. There was a lot of short interest in the sto=
ck, which attracts meme buyers. When Robinhood restricted purchases of Game=
Stop Corp. and other meme stocks in late January, as the meme stocks were m=
elting up, Naked was on the list; when Robinhood narrowed the list to only =
the eight memeiest stocks, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/25638771.285655/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbG=
VzLzIwMjEtMDEtMzEvcm9iaW5ob29kLW5hcnJvd3MtdHJhZGluZy1yZXN0cmljdGlvbnMtdG8tO=
C1jb21wYW5pZXMtZnJvbS01MD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTA5MjFfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVt=
PWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMTExMDkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWd=
uPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf455b6b4" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Naked was one =
of them</a>.[1] It=E2=80=99s an inner-circle meme stock.</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">One result of becoming a meme stock is that you can=C2=A0<em>=
raise money</em>. At the end of January, Naked <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25638771.285655/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9Bcm=
NoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzAwMDE3MDc5MTkvMDAwMTQ5MzE1MjIxMDAyMjQzL2V4OTktMS5od=
G0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa169c62e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">raised $50 million</a> by sel=
ling stock at $1.70 per share, higher than the stock had traded in a year. =
A month later, it <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
25638771.285655/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzAwMDE=
3MDc5MTkvMDAwMTQ5MzE1MjIxMDA0NzkwL2Zvcm02LWsuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
a29983fb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgro=
und-color: #ccc;">raised another $100 million</a> in a private placement at=
 about $0.93 per share.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One result of becom=
ing a meme stock and raising money is that you can just=C2=A0<em>do somethi=
ng different</em>. Instead of being an online intimates-and-swimwear retail=
er, you can be =E2=80=A6=C2=A0I am reading here =E2=80=9Can electric-car co=
mpany=E2=80=9D? <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25=
638771.285655/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYWZyLmNvbS9jb21wYW5pZXMvcmV0YWlsL3JlZGRpdC1md=
WVsbGVkLW1lbWUtc3RvY2stc3dhcHMtbGluZ2VyaWUtZm9yLWV2cy0yMDIxMTEwNS1wNTk2YnE/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa244f4b6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Okay sure</a>:</p><blockquote><p=
 style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Reddit-fuelled meme stock Naked Brand Group has =
acquired US-based electric vehicle startup Cenntro Auto Group in a reverse-=
scrip deal giving the former lingerie penny stock exposure to one of the ho=
ttest new tech themes.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Nasdaq-listed li=
ngerie company, once behind brands such as Loveable and Pleasure State, sho=
t to fame after Reddit traders piled in following =E2=80=9Cmeme-stock=E2=80=
=9D euphoria in early 2021, ballooning its shareholder base to over 900,000=
 investors.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On Tuesday, Naked Brand announc=
ed it would swap 70 per cent of its outstanding shares plus $US282 million =
=E2=80=A6 for Cenntro Auto, an electric vehicle developer that has built an=
d sold 4,000 commercial electric vehicles.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"marg=
in: 16px 0;">Here is the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/25638771.285655/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRh=
LzAwMDE3MDc5MTkvMDAwMTQ5MzE1MjIxMDI3NTMyL2V4OTktMS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB929b366c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">announcement</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">Naked Brand Group Limited (NASDAQ:NAKD) (=E2=80=9CNaked=E2=80=9D=
 or the =E2=80=9CCompany=E2=80=9D) and privately-held Cenntro Automotive Gr=
oup, Inc. (=E2=80=9CCenntro=E2=80=9D), today announced that the companies h=
ave entered into a definitive agreement under which Naked will acquire the =
outstanding stock in three entities comprising Cenntro Automotive Group (=
=E2=80=9CCenntro=E2=80=9D), a commercial EV technology company with advance=
d market-validated commercial vehicles and autonomous driving technologies =
in a Stock for Stock Acquisition Agreement (the =E2=80=9CTransaction=E2=80=
=9D). Upon completion of the Transaction, the Company is expected to change=
 its name to Cenntro Automotive Group (CAG). The Company expects to retain =
its Nasdaq listing and ticker symbol =E2=80=9CNAKD=E2=80=9D.</p></blockquot=
e><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yeah I mean of course it will keep the ticke=
r; the ticker has done a lot for it. You=E2=80=99d better believe that (1) =
the stock is up (up about 14% as of 11 a.m. today) and (2) Naked <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25638771.285655/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzAwMDE3MDc5MTkvMDAwMTQ5MzE1MjIxMDI=
3NTMzL2Zvcm00MjRiNS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa47cc419" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">launche=
d a $300 million at-the-market stock offering</a>=C2=A0this morning to rais=
e the cash for the deal.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t kn=
ow! Capitalism is different now! It used to be that, if you were a struggli=
ng online lingerie retailer, you could try to sell more lingerie, or you co=
uld try to cut your costs of selling lingerie, or you could expand into som=
e related apparel business lines, or you could shut down, I don't know, I=
=E2=80=99m sure there were more options, but if you went to an investment c=
onference and said =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m tired of lingerie let=E2=80=99s do =
electric cars=E2=80=9D investors would be skeptical. But now sometimes you =
can be a struggling online lingerie retailer and get hit by Reddit lightnin=
g. And if that happens, you gotta seize the moment. =E2=80=9CPeople are pay=
ing attention to us, we can raise money, only one choice here: electric car=
s.=E2=80=9D (Honestly two choices: electric cars or crypto.) And off you go=
. Now you run an electric-car company. Congratulations.</p><p style=3D"marg=
in: 16px 0;">I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/256=
38771.285655/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMj=
EtMDYtMjgvaW52ZXN0b3JzLXdpbGwtYnV5LWFueXRoaW5nLW5vdz9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTA5MjFfT=
U9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVy=
bT0yMTExMDkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4368b3=
a4" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> wrote about</a> meme-stock pivots in June:</p><blockquote><p =
style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One way to read that story is that AMC and GameSt=
op are currently in businesses that are bad, as evidenced by the fact that =
they lose money. They would like to get into businesses that are good, in d=
ifferent ways. (AMC by buying up theaters to double down on its current bus=
iness, as far as I can tell; GameStop by mysteriously transforming into som=
e sort of tech company.) Three years ago that was a hard sell: It was not e=
asy for a public company to go to investors and say =E2=80=9Chey it turns o=
ut that the business we are in loses money, we would like to get into a dif=
ferent business, would you finance that?=E2=80=9D Now =E2=80=A6=C2=A0I am n=
ot sure it=E2=80=99s easy, but it=E2=80=99s certainly easier.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One way for GameStop to pivot might be=C2=A0to use all=
 the money it can raise to go=C2=A0<em>buy=C2=A0</em>a tech company. People=
 have pointed out that it is almost an informal=C2=A0SPAC, a special purpos=
e acquisition company, in that it has=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/25638771.285655/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS=
9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDYtMjIvZ2FtZXN0b3AtanVtcHMtYWZ0ZXItcmFpc2luZy0xL=
TEtYmlsbGlvbi1pbi1zdG9jay1zYWxlLXByb2dyYW0_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEwOTIxX01PTkVZU1RV=
RkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjExMTA=
5JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB14329900" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">raised a billion dollars</a>=C2=A0with no cle=
ar use of proceeds and can now, if it wants, use that money to buy into a n=
ew business.=C2=A0GameStop has raised so much money that its current expert=
ise in mall-based video-game retail (a declining industry!) doesn=E2=80=99t=
 matter; it can hire all-new expertise in the form of=C2=A0<a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25638771.285655/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYm=
xvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDYtMTAvbWF5YmUtZ2FtZXN0b3Ata=
XMtZ29vZC1ub3c_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEwOTIxX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1=
dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjExMTA5JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN=
0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2ba9617c" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">an executive team poached from Amazon</a>, and then go out and acquire a =
not-at-all-mall-based business, and just become a new company. Because shar=
eholders will cheerfully fund it.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin:=
 16px 0;">Same with Naked, except Naked went and did it. If you are a SPAC,=
 the highest and best use of your money is generally to take an electric-ve=
hicle company public. If you are an informal SPAC =E2=80=94=C2=A0a meme sto=
ck that raised a pot of money on retail investor enthusiasm and wants to us=
e the money to pivot to a new line of business =E2=80=94=C2=A0the same logi=
c applies. If you=E2=80=99re a meme lingerie company, now you=E2=80=99re a =
meme electric-vehicle company. You keep your meme ticker though.</p><table =
